  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large terracotta dish over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onion and garlic and sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken livers and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken broth, Croatian paprika, dried thyme, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.",
    "Preheat the broiler.",
    "Stir the stew to combine, then top with shredded provolone cheese and broil until golden brown, about 2-3 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Let the stew rest for a few minutes before serving, as it will continue to thicken and the flavors will meld together."
